On Wed, 24 May 2006, Scott Lyons wrote:

> On 5/24/06 6:56 PM, "Old Volks Home" <oldvolkshome(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:
>
> > 20/50 might be the way to go, but I've run 40wt for years in the 2 liter
> > with no ill effects.  In the very hot triple digit weather of Northern Cal
> > in August/September I even ran 50wt in my 80 Vanagon.

Keep in mind that thick oil also flows through the oil cooler slower, so
running 50W might make your engine run a bit hotter than 40W.  As long as
the oil can maintain good pressure it doesn't help to run higher numbers.

I run 10W40 year round, mostly in SoCal, but sometimes in Nevada.

George
